TOOLS INSTALLATION

System Requirements
 6 GB RAM
 50 GB HDD
 Ubuntu 20.04+
 4vCPU

1. Yosys - RTL Synthesis
Yosys is an Open-Source logic synthesis framework that converts Register-Transfer Level hardware descriptions, 
primarily Verilog, into gate-level netlists suitable for physical implementation.

Yosys Installation

$ sudo apt-get update
$ git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys.git
$ cd yosys
$ sudo apt install make (If make is not installed please install it)
$ sudo apt-get install build-essential clang bison flex \
 libreadline-dev gawk tcl-dev libffi-dev git \
 graphviz xdot pkg-config python3 libboost-system-dev \
 libboost-python-dev libboost-filesystem-dev zlib1g-dev
$ make config-gcc
$ make
$ sudo make install 

2. Iverilog
Iverilog is an Open-Source Verilog compiler and simulator that is used for Digital Circuit Design and Verification.

Iverilog Installation

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install iverilog 

3. GTKWave
GTKWave is used for graphical waveform viewer, for post-mortem analysis of Digital Simulation Models, primarily for Verilog and VHDL>

GTKWave Installation

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt install gtkwave 

4. Ngspice 
Ngspice is an Electronic Circuit Simulator that numerically solves circuit equations to analyze time-varying currents and voltages, 
noise and small signal behavior.

Ngspice Installation

After downloading the tarball from https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/ to a local directory, unpack it using:
$ tar -zxvf ngspice-37.tar.gz
$ cd ngspice-37
$ mkdir release
$ cd release
$ ../configure  --with-x --with-readline=yes --disable-debug
$ make
$ sudo make install

5. Magic
Magic is an VLSI Layout editor for interactive design, background design-rule checking, and built-in circuit extraction.

Magic Installation

# Install the required dependencies:
$ sudo apt-get install m4
$ sudo apt-get install tcsh
$ sudo apt-get install csh
$ sudo apt-get install libx11-dev
$ sudo apt-get install tcl-dev tk-dev
$ sudo apt-get install libcairo2-dev
$ sudo apt-get install mesa-common-dev libglu1-mesa-dev
$ sudo apt-get install libncurses-dev

# Clone Magic repository:
$ git clone https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/magic
$ cd magic

# Configure build
$ ./configure

# Build Magic
$ make

# Install system
$ sudo make install

Tool Versions
$ git --version
$ docker --version
$ python3 --version
$ python3 -m pip --version
$ make --version























